Business Brief -- Alza Corp.:
   Company Reports Deficits
   For Fourth Quarter, Year
For the full year, Alza reported a loss of $62.1 million,
or 88 cents a share, against 1990 profit of $24.7 million, or
35 cents a share, on a 48% rise in revenue to $162.3 million
from $109.4 million.
   The one-time charge, which was previously announced, was
related to the acquisition of Bio-Electro Systems Inc. and
certain restructuring of its relationship with On-Site
Therapeutics Inc.